    Wiki (Links & Infos)
    ​
    Here you can find informations and links for each project involved with Revanced.
    If you are wondering which one to install ReVanced or ReVanced Extended, my suggestion is to go with the official ReVanced, check     this post.​
    Differences ReVanced vs ReVanced Extended (inotia00, YT-Advanced, anddea, rufusin)

    • ReVanced is the main original project.
    • ReVanced Extended (RVX) by inotia00 started as fork of ReVanced with more patches etc. which were useful back then when ReVanced didn't had some useful patches. Stil some exclusive patches of RVX are great and useful.
    • YT-Advanced, anddea, rufusin etc. patches, are forks of the ReVanced Extended and started when inotia00 decided to stopped (but now inotia00 is back). Usually they had some patches more & couple of changes and were updated in more recent yt version. You can check some differences anddea vs inotia00 patches here.
    • So the timeline is: ReVanced (Original project) > ReVanced Extended by inotia00 (fork of ReVanced) > YT-Advanced (fork of ReVanced Extended) > anddea (fork of ReX) > rufusin (fork anddea).
    • If you want to use ReVanced Extended now, use either inotia00 which is the main dev of Extended or the alternative anddea patches. Both of these are updated.
    • If you ask me, ReVanced or ReVanced Extended, I would say ReVanced, but that's my personal opinion. Check here why.

    GmsCore/MicroG

    Free implementation of Play Services . Necessary services to run ReVanced as Non-Root.
    • GmsCore by ReVanced: The Official ReVanced GmsCore services.
    • MicroG RE by WTSXda: Fork designed for ReVanced with Material You design, along with some improvements and features.
    • GmsCore by YT-Advanced.

    ReVanced

    ReVanced is a modular patcher for apps such as YouTube but only. This project was born out of Vanced's discontinuation and the goal is to continue the legacy of what Vanced left. ​
    • Developers/Contributors: ReVanced Team
    • Website: ReVanced Website
    • Github: ReVanced
    • Patches: ReVanced Patches
    • Integrations: ReVanced Integrations
    • Tools: ReVanced Manager / ReVanced CLI / CLI Automation by taku Moderator of ReVanced Team.
    • Supported Versions of the Apps: Target Versions
    • Documentation: ReVanced Megathread
    • Support: Discord / Telegram / Reddit
    • Localization - Translation Platform: Crowdin
    • Donation

    ReVanced Extended Project & Forks

    ReVanced Extended (aka RVX) is a derivative project of ReVanced (not affiliated), mainly consisting of patches made for YouTube, YT Music, and Reddit. It focuses on providing more features than the ReVanced patches. The founder of ReVanced Extended is inotia00, however there are several forks/adaptions of ReVanced Extended made by other developers.​
    ReVanced Extended (RVX) by inotia00

    • Developers/Contributors: inotia00
    • Patches: inotia00 Patches
    • Integrations: inotia00 Integrations
    • Tools: RVX Manager / RVX Builder / Revancify / CLI Automation
    • Support: Telegram Group / RVX Notification Channel / Reddit / Discord
    • Documentation: RVX Documentation / ReVanced Extended Features / ReVanced-Extended-Community - Patches-Documentation / Extended Custom Icons List
    • Localazition - Translation Platform: RVX Crowdin / RVX Music Crowdin

    For root users microg is not needed
    (Needed Only when rom does not come with gms by default)

    For root or non root,
    user's should download nodpi varient of YouTube as revanced manager currently cannot patch dpi version.

    For official revanced
    user's should not select debug patch as it may lead to performance degradation.

    For revanced extended,
    developer recommends selecting all patches and configuring yt app per user requirement.

    Root users would need detach magisk module to prevent YouTube update from playstore.

    Revanced manager has an option to export log and patched YouTube option available.

    User's should use them...
    logs for communicating any errors
    Patched app for reinstallation if required

    Retrial said:
    I have added as optional step, But I am pretty sure not gonna hurt even if root users install Vanced microG.
    ........
    The only point to install MicroG is to be able to sign into ReVanced on an unrooted device. If you're rooted Google Play Services will ensure that. MicroG is always active (like it's google pendant) and therefore using battery. So I recommend: If you're rooted don't install it.

    Retrial said:
    What's the point of that step? ReVanced isn't using different packange name anyway? Anyway, I've included this near patches as recommended documentation to read.
    On rooted devices ReVanced may replace the original YT (if you don't use a different package name). In that case playstore will try to update it. The mindetach module will prevent that:

    GitHub - j-hc/mindetach-magisk: Simpler and better Magisk module to detach apps from Play Store

    Simpler and better Magisk module to detach apps from Play Store - j-hc/mindetach-magisk
    github.com
